sec.p:
Before assessing the results of the one-way analysis of covariance (ANCOVA) and variance (ANOVA), the analysis of Student's standardized residuals was examined to detect outliers (values greater than or equal to three standard deviations). The normality of errors and the homogeneity of variances between treatments for the variables were previously assessed using the Shapiro–Wilk and Levene tests, respectively. For the growth performance variables, the statistical model used was: Yijk = µ + Ti + bj + β (Xijk -\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
